Welcome to Lazard World Trust Fund







  Home









                Welcome
              

Lazard World Trust Fund (previously known as The World Trust Fund) seeks to achieve long-term capital appreciation by investing primarily in companies whose shares trade at a discount to their underlying net asset value. These include closed-end funds and investment trusts, holding companies, and special situation companies. The team encourages boards to enhance shareholder value and seeks to reduce or eliminate discounts through improved corporate governance and, where appropriate, corporate restructuring. Since 2000, the Fund has also hedged a portion of the underlying market exposure.







                      More About Lazard World Trust Fund
                    










